docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:93:## BDD Proof Scenarios
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:95:## Feature 1: Harness choice does not change dispatch semantics
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:97:### Scenario 1.1: A valid dispatch executes through Harness A
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:103:### Scenario 1.2: Equivalent dispatch executes through Harness B
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:109:### Scenario 1.3: Unsupported harness action is denied safely
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:117:## Feature 2: Environment choice does not change dispatch semantics
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:119:### Scenario 2.1: Dispatch executes in one environment type
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:125:### Scenario 2.2: Equivalent dispatch executes in a second environment type
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:131:### Scenario 2.3: Unavailable/incompatible environment is rejected safely
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:139:## Feature 3: Execution evidence is normalized and safe to persist
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:141:### Scenario 3.1: Operators receive normalized lifecycle signals
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:147:### Scenario 3.2: Adapter-specific failures map to typed Tanren failure classes
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:153:### Scenario 3.3: Sensitive output is redacted before durable persistence
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:161:## Feature 4: Lease lifecycle is safe across all terminal paths
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:163:### Scenario 4.1: Success releases environment lease cleanly
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:169:### Scenario 4.2: Failure or cancellation still releases lease cleanly
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:175:### Scenario 4.3: Crash recovery prevents orphaned or duplicate execution
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:183:## Feature 5: Worker execution is durable and policy-driven
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:185:### Scenario 5.1: Accepted work is consumed and completed durably
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:191:### Scenario 5.2: Retryable failures follow explicit retry policy
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:197:### Scenario 5.3: Non-retryable failures stop without hidden retries
docs/rewrite/PHASE1_PROOF_BDD.md:205:## Feature 6: Phase 1 end-to-end reliability can be demonstrated
